### Test React Agent via LangGraph API
### Make sure the LangGraph server is running (npm run dev:langgraph)

### 1. Search for assistants
POST http://localhost:2024/assistants/search
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 2. Create a new thread
POST http://localhost:2024/threads
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "metadata": {
    "test": "true"
  }
}

###

### 3. Run the agent (replace THREAD_ID with ID from step 2)
POST http://localhost:2024/threads/{THREAD_ID}/runs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assistant_id": "react-agent",
  "input": {
    "messages": [
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "Search for the latest news about artificial intelligence and summarize the top 3 findings"
      }
    ]
  }
}

###

### 4. Stream the agent execution (replace THREAD_ID and RUN_ID)
GET http://localhost:2024/threads/{THREAD_ID}/runs/{RUN_ID}/stream

###

### 5. Get thread state (replace THREAD_ID)
GET http://localhost:2024/threads/{THREAD_ID}/state
